[eerie, tense music]

1197
00:58:25.573 --> 00:58:33.573
♪

1198
00:58:35.532 --> 00:58:38.323
No! No!

1199
00:58:38.407 --> 00:58:40.907
No!

1200
00:58:40.990 --> 00:58:43.490
[camera shutter clicking]

1201
00:58:43.573 --> 00:58:44.948
♪

1202
00:58:45.032 --> 00:58:47.157
[bag zippering,
stretcher clattering]


1203
00:58:47.240 --> 00:58:52.031
Then, we met him in the woods
near Cordovo Beach.


1204
00:58:52.032 --> 00:58:53.490
He tried to catch him.

1205
00:58:54.698 --> 00:58:56.240
And he got away.

1206
00:58:56.323 --> 00:58:58.282
[Detective] You should
have called the police.


1207
00:58:58.365 --> 00:59:00.573
[Sarah]
I did. Twice.


1208
00:59:00.615 --> 00:59:02.073
They were no help.

1209
00:59:04.865 --> 00:59:08.073
[Detective] So you
think this Mr. Speedo character


1210
00:59:08.198 --> 00:59:10.240
is the one who killed
you boyfriend?


1211
00:59:12.615 --> 00:59:14.948
[Sarah]
More than likely.


1212
00:59:15.032 --> 00:59:16.466
[Detective] Can't think
of anyone else who might have


1213
00:59:16.490 --> 00:59:17.740
had a reason to kill Tony?

1214
00:59:17.782 --> 00:59:20.573
[indistinct radio chatter]

1215
00:59:20.657 --> 00:59:23.240
- No.
- How 'bout your ex-husband?


1216
00:59:23.323 --> 00:59:24.740
He just got out.

1217
00:59:24.823 --> 00:59:29.407
He tried to kill you,
what, 13 months ago.


1218
00:59:29.490 --> 00:59:32.032
You think maybe he had a problem
with you dating someone new?


1219
00:59:33.740 --> 00:59:35.198
Maybe.

1220
00:59:35.282 --> 00:59:36.882
[Detective]
You don't seem too convinced.


1221
00:59:38.532 --> 00:59:41.615
Let's just say my ex-husband's
turned a corner.


1222
00:59:41.698 --> 00:59:42.966
[Detective]
How would you know that?


1223
00:59:42.990 --> 00:59:44.490
Have you seen him?

1224
00:59:44.573 --> 00:59:47.240
- You talk to him?
- Yes.


1225
00:59:47.323 --> 00:59:49.573
[Detective] So he
violated his restraining order.


1226
00:59:49.698 --> 00:59:51.198
He was...

1227
00:59:53.032 --> 00:59:55.240
- well-behaved.
- That's irrelevant.


1228
00:59:55.282 --> 00:59:57.740
You need to tell us
when he contacts you.


1229
00:59:57.823 --> 01:00:00.073
Did you and Tony get into
a fight last night?


1230
01:00:00.157 --> 01:00:01.532
I know what you are implying.

1231
01:00:01.615 --> 01:00:03.407
Please don't go there.

1232
01:00:03.448 --> 01:00:05.115
You were the last person to see
him alive.


1233
01:00:05.198 --> 01:00:08.948
[Sarah]
No, we did not get into a fight.


1234
01:00:09.073 --> 01:00:12.907
Truth is, I was starting
to fall for him.


1235
01:00:12.990 --> 01:00:14.907
There, I said it.

1236
01:00:14.990 --> 01:00:16.299
Now I'm not gonna say
another word


1237
01:00:16.323 --> 01:00:18.198
until I'm sitting next
to my lawyer.


1238
01:00:19.948 --> 01:00:22.282
[indistinct radio chatter]

1239
01:00:22.365 --> 01:00:24.823
[Detective] Found
a knife out front in the bushes.


1240
01:00:24.907 --> 01:00:27.073
Gonna run the biometrics
and get back to ya.


1241
01:00:28.323 --> 01:00:30.407
If I were you,
I wouldn't leave town.


1242
01:00:31.532 --> 01:00:32.907
Got a place to stay?

1243
01:00:35.823 --> 01:00:38.907
Yeah. Right here.

1244
01:00:38.990 --> 01:00:40.948
[Alice]
You can't stay there.


1245
01:00:41.032 --> 01:00:43.406
Sarah, it's not safe.

1246
01:00:43.407 --> 01:00:45.990
I told you, I'm not gonna hide
from this anymore.


1247
01:00:46.073 --> 01:00:48.948
I heard that before,
but this getting ridiculous.


1248
01:00:49.073 --> 01:00:50.424
What, your boyfriend
was stabbed to death


1249
01:00:50.448 --> 01:00:51.907
while you were sleeping.

1250
01:00:51.990 --> 01:00:53.448
Did that detective call you?

1251
01:00:53.532 --> 01:00:55.448
Yes. I gave him my statement

1252
01:00:55.532 --> 01:00:58.198
and he said there's no reason
for me to drive up there.


1253
01:00:58.282 --> 01:01:01.823
You need to get out of there
and come back to LA now.


1254
01:01:01.907 --> 01:01:03.407
No, I'm not leaving here

1255
01:01:03.573 --> 01:01:04.990
until I catch whoever did this.

1256
01:01:05.073 --> 01:01:06.947
[Alice]
Do you hear what you're saying?


1257
01:01:06.948 --> 01:01:09.240
That's the stupidest idea
I have ever heard.


1258
01:01:09.282 --> 01:01:10.657
It's a matter of principle.

1259
01:01:10.782 --> 01:01:12.591
[Alice] No, it's a matter
of you being an idiot.


1260
01:01:12.615 --> 01:01:13.948
I am not being an idiot.

1261
01:01:14.032 --> 01:01:15.591
[Alice] You were an idiot
to marry Miles,


1262
01:01:15.615 --> 01:01:18.157
you were an idiot to wallow
in your depression for a year,


1263
01:01:18.282 --> 01:01:20.323
and now you're an idiot
to play junior detective.


1264
01:01:20.407 --> 01:01:21.740
[Sarah]
I have to figure this out.


1265
01:01:21.823 --> 01:01:23.198
Don't you get it?

1266
01:01:23.282 --> 01:01:25.049
I don't know who really
attacked me last year.


1267
01:01:25.073 --> 01:01:26.615
I don't know who killed Tony.

1268
01:01:26.740 --> 01:01:28.365
For all I know,
you could have done it.


1269
01:01:28.448 --> 01:01:30.990
[tense music]

1270
01:01:31.073 --> 01:01:32.532
- Me?
- Yeah, you.


1271
01:01:32.615 --> 01:01:34.740
Did the police tell you
that Tony was stabbed?


1272
01:01:34.782 --> 01:01:38.782
♪

1273
01:01:38.907 --> 01:01:41.031
- No.
- Well, I didn't either.


1274
01:01:41.032 --> 01:01:42.424
How did you know
that Tony was stabbed?


1275
01:01:42.448 --> 01:01:44.088
How do you know
he wasn't shot with a gun?


1276
01:01:44.157 --> 01:01:45.490
You think I'm a murderer?

1277
01:01:45.573 --> 01:01:47.091
I think I saw you
beat the hell out of Miles


1278
01:01:47.115 --> 01:01:48.865
on the beach and then threaten
to kill him.


1279
01:01:48.948 --> 01:01:50.947
I was protecting my best friend.

1280
01:01:50.948 --> 01:01:53.240
[Sarah] Were you?
Or was it something else?


1281
01:01:53.323 --> 01:01:55.282
[Alice] Come on,
it's me you're talking to.


1282
01:01:55.365 --> 01:01:56.739
♪

1283
01:01:56.740 --> 01:01:58.740
I've never even met Tony
in person.


1284
01:01:58.823 --> 01:02:01.240
What reason would I have
to kill him?


1285
01:02:01.323 --> 01:02:03.032
I don't know.

1286
01:02:03.115 --> 01:02:05.532
I'm sorry. I'm just...

1287
01:02:05.615 --> 01:02:07.907
[Alice] Look, what you're going
through is overwhelming


1288
01:02:07.990 --> 01:02:10.698
and you're confused,
but you need to come home.


1289
01:02:10.782 --> 01:02:13.032
In fact, I'm ordering you.

1290
01:02:13.115 --> 01:02:16.865
Get out of my house now
and come back to LA.


1291
01:02:16.948 --> 01:02:19.782
[Sarah] No. I am on vacation
and I'm gonna catch this guy,


1292
01:02:19.865 --> 01:02:21.115
and you can't stop me.

1293
01:02:21.198 --> 01:02:23.782
You're not my mother,
you're my agent.


1294
01:02:23.865 --> 01:02:25.573
Not anymore I'm not.

1295
01:02:25.657 --> 01:02:26.865
What are you talking about?

1296
01:02:26.948 --> 01:02:28.407
♪

1297
01:02:28.448 --> 01:02:31.657
I had to tell
the partners what happened.


1298
01:02:31.740 --> 01:02:33.865
And that you need another year
to finish the book.


1299
01:02:33.948 --> 01:02:36.573
- At least that.
- Everybody went nuts


1300
01:02:36.698 --> 01:02:38.865
and we lost the deal
with the publisher.


1301
01:02:38.948 --> 01:02:42.657
I'm sorry, babes, we have
to drop you from the agency.


1302
01:02:42.740 --> 01:02:44.424
[Sarah] So not only does
my boyfriend get murdered


1303
01:02:44.448 --> 01:02:46.073
this morning,
my best friend is firing me


1304
01:02:46.157 --> 01:02:48.948
because some crazy fan
stole my computer.


1305
01:02:49.032 --> 01:02:51.865
- What a day.
